sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as KServe Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as KServe Controller<br/>Leader Election
    participant Init as storage-initializer<br/>Init Container
    participant S3 as S3/GCS Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Activator as Knative Activator<br/>8012/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant Agent as kserve-agent<br/>9081/TCP HTTP
    participant Model as Model Server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CloudEvents as CloudEvents Sink<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (optional)
    participant Router as InferenceGraph Router<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS

    %% Flow 1: InferenceService Creation
    Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: InferenceService Creation and Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: POST InferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (user SA)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
    Webhook->>Webhook: Apply defaults<br/>(runtime, resources)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated InferenceService
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate spec<br/>(storage URI, runtime)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response
    K8sAPI-->>User: InferenceService created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch InferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: InferenceService event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Knative Service<br/>or Deployment
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio VirtualService
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service

    %% Flow 2: Model Initialization
    Note over Init,Model: Flow 2: Model Initialization and Serving
    Init->>S3: GET model artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS SigV4 / GCP IAM
    S3-->>Init: Model files (.pb, .pth, etc)
    Init->>Init: Write to EmptyDir volume<br/>/mnt/models
    Init-->>Model: Init complete

    Model->>Model: Load model from<br/>/mnt/models
    Model->>Agent: Readiness probe<br/>localhost:8080
    Agent-->>Model: Ready
    Agent->>K8sAPI: Update Pod status<br/>Ready

    %% Flow 3: Inference Request
    Note over User,CloudEvents: Flow 3: Inference Request (via Istio/Knative)
    User->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS 443 TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    Gateway->>Gateway: TLS Termination<br/>RequestAuthentication
    Gateway->>Activator: Forward request<br/>HTTP mTLS (Istio)
    Activator->>Activator: Scale from zero<br/>if needed
    Activator->>Agent: HTTP/8012 mTLS<br/>via queue-proxy
    Agent->>Agent: Request batching<br/>(optional)
    Agent->>Model: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTP 8080 localhost
    Model->>Model: Run inference<br/>(TensorFlow/PyTorch)
    Model-->>Agent: Prediction JSON
    Agent->>CloudEvents: POST request/response log<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Agent-->>Activator: Prediction result
    Activator-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: JSON response

    %% Flow 4: InferenceGraph
    Note over User,Router: Flow 4: InferenceGraph Router Workflow
    User->>Router: POST /v2/models/graph/infer<br/>HTTP mTLS (Istio)
    Router->>Router: Parse routing logic<br/>(sequence/switch/ensemble)
    Router->>Agent: Step 1: Preprocessing<br/>HTTP 80 mTLS
    Agent->>Model: Forward to model<br/>HTTP 8080 localhost
    Model-->>Agent: Preprocessed data
    Agent-->>Router: Step 1 result
    Router->>Agent: Step 2: Prediction<br/>HTTP 80 mTLS
    Agent->>Model: Forward to model<br/>HTTP 8080 localhost
    Model-->>Agent: Prediction
    Agent-->>Router: Step 2 result
    Router->>Router: Aggregate results<br/>(if ensemble)
    Router-->>User: Final response
